# ==========================================
# 1. THE NUKE (Ignore Everything)
# ==========================================
*

# ==========================================
# 2. DIRECTORY TRAVERSAL
# ==========================================
# You must un-ignore all directories so Git can actually look 
# inside them to find your allowed files.
!*/

# ==========================================
# 3. THE WHITELIST (Allowed File Types)
# ==========================================
# Now un-ignore the specific file types you care about.
!*.png
!*.ipynb
!*.py
!*.md
!*.csv
!*.pkl
!*.txt

# Always un-ignore the .gitignore file itself so your rules are pushed!
!.gitignore

# ==========================================
# 4. THE EXCLUSIONS (Re-ignoring bad folders)
# ==========================================
# Because you un-ignored all folders in Step 2, Git will try to track 
# any .py or .png files inside your virtual environments or caches. 
# We must explicitly re-ignore those specific folders.
venv/
.venv/
__pycache__/
.ipynb_checkpoints/
.vscode/
.idea/